---
title: Home
---
{% extends '_base.njk' %}

{% block body %}
<style>
  * {
    color: #0f0;
  }
  
  body {
    font-family: monospace;
    background: #111;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    overflow-x: hidden;
    text-align: center;
    padding-bottom: 5em;
  }
  
  main {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px;
  }
  
  .glitch {
    font-size: 80px;
    font-weight: bold;
    position: relative;
    text-shadow: 0.05em 0 0 rgba(255,0,0,.75), 
                -0.025em -0.05em 0 rgba(0,255,0,.75),
                0.025em 0.05em 0 rgba(0,0,255,.75);
    animation: glitch 5000ms infinite;
  }
  
  @keyframes glitch {
    0% {
      text-shadow: 0.05em 0 0 rgba(255,0,0,.75),
                  -0.025em -0.05em 0 rgba(0,255,0,.75),
                  0.025em 0.05em 0 rgba(0,0,255,.75);
    }
    14% {
      text-shadow: 0.05em 0 0 rgba(255,0,0,.75),
                  -0.025em -0.05em 0 rgba(0,255,0,.75),
                  0.025em 0.05em 0 rgba(0,0,255,.75);
    }
    15% {
      text-shadow: -0.05em -0.025em 0 rgba(255,0,0,.75),
                  0.025em 0.025em 0 rgba(0,255,0,.75),
                  -0.05em -0.05em 0 rgba(0,0,255,.75);
    }
    49% {
      text-shadow: -0.05em -0.025em 0 rgba(255,0,0,.75),
                  0.025em 0.025em 0 rgba(0,255,0,.75),
                  -0.05em -0.05em 0 rgba(0,0,255,.75);
    }
    50% {
      text-shadow: 0.025em 0.05em 0 rgba(255,0,0,.75),
                  0.05em 0 0 rgba(0,255,0,.75),
                  0 -0.05em 0 rgba(0,0,255,.75);
    }
    99% {
      text-shadow: 0.025em 0.05em 0 rgba(255,0,0,.75),
                  0.05em 0 0 rgba(0,255,0,.75),
                  0 -0.05em 0 rgba(0,0,255,.75);
    }
    100% {
      text-shadow: -0.025em 0 0 rgba(255,0,0,.75),
                  -0.025em -0.025em 0 rgba(0,255,0,.75),
                  -0.025em -0.05em 0 rgba(0,0,255,.75);
    }
  }
  
  .ascii-art {
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 12px;
    white-space: pre;
    margin: 40px auto;
    max-width: 600px;
  }
  
  .crt-lines {
    position: fixed;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    z-index: 999;
    pointer-events: none;
    background: linear-gradient(rgba(18, 16, 16, 0) 50%, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25) 50%);
    background-size: 100% 4px;
  }
  
  .crt-flicker {
    position: fixed;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    z-index: 1000;
    pointer-events: none;
    animation: flicker 0.15s infinite;
    opacity: 0.1;
  }
  
  @keyframes flicker {
    0% { opacity: 0.1; }
    50% { opacity: 0; }
    100% { opacity: 0.1; }
  }
  
  .tagline {
    font-size: 24px;
    margin: 40px 0;
  }
  
  .features {
    margin: auto;
    font-size: 18px;
    
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    width: fit-content;
  }
  
  .feature {
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: start;
  }
  
  .feature:before {
    content: ">";
    margin-right: 10px;
    animation: blink 1s step-end infinite;
  }
  
  @keyframes blink {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50% { opacity: 0; }
  }
  
  .action {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 30px;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    background: #0f0;
    color: #000;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: bold;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.3s;
  }
  
  .action:hover {
    background: #000;
    color: #0f0;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px #0f0, 0 0 20px #0f0;
  }
  
  .footer {
    margin-top: 60px;
    font-size: 14px;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }
</style>

<div class="crt-lines"></div>
<div class="crt-flicker"></div>

<main>
  <header>
    <h1 class="glitch">PicoSSG</h1>
  </header>
  
  <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
    <code>npx @wolframkriesing/picossg -c content -o output</code>
  </div>
  
  <div class="tagline">
    The anti-framework static site generator.
    <br>No config. No nonsense.
    <br>Just files in, files out.
  </div>
  
  <div class="features">
    <div class="feature">1:1 file mapping â€“ what you see is what you get</div>
    <div class="feature">Markdown? Yes. Nunjucks? Yes. Both? Yes.</div>
    <div class="feature">Files+dirs starting with _ are private. That's it.</div>
    <div class="feature">Builds faster than you can say "overengineered"</div>
    <div class="feature">Aimed for no magic. Capped at {{ srcStats.numLoc }} LOC</div>
  </div>
  
  <div style="text-align: center; font-size: 2rem;">
    <a href="/docs" class="action">READ THE DOCS</a>
  </div>
  
  <div class="footer">
    PicoSSG - Built for humans who just want static sites without the drama.
  </div>
  
  <div class="ascii-art">
    {% include '_picossg_asciiart.txt' %}
    <br/>  
    v{{ _site.picoSsgVersion }}
  </div>
</main>
  
<footer>
  <a href="/changelog">Changelog</a>
  <a href="/docs">Docs</a>
  <a href="https://codeberg.org/wolframkriesing/picossg">Source code</a>
  <a href="https://mastodontech.de/@wolframkriesing">Contact</a>
</footer>

{% endblock %}
